<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>The Austria Discovery</h2>
<p><strong>11 nights from £999</strong>*</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><strong>Kitzbühel (4 nights) - Zell am See (3 nights) - St. Wolfgang (4 nights) - Salzburg (3 nights optional)<br /></strong><strong>A fascinating tour showcasing Austria’s most iconic and best known resorts.</strong> Start in the pretty Tyrolean town of Kitzbühel, world famous in winter for its downhill ski race, and in summer a peaceful oasis nestled amongst some of the best walking in the Tyrol, with a beautiful medieval centre. Following a scenic train ride, Zell am See is one of Austria’s best loved lake resorts and a popular centre for shopping and boat trips, set against a stunning lakes and mountains backdrop. On Saturday transfer to the idyllic resort of St. Wolfgang with its pretty painted houses for rest and relaxation on your private lakeside lido. Take a steamboat ride across the lake, a cog railway up the Schafberg mountain or enjoy a classical music concert. Finish your holiday here or spend a few days taking in the sights of historic Salzburg. *Hotel Schweizerhof, Kitzbühel, Hotel Seehof, Zell am See &amp; Strandhotel Margaretha, St. Wolfgang. Other combinations are available.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>The Austria Explorer</h2>
<p><strong>14 nights from £999*</strong></p>
<div style="columns: 100px 2; -webkit-columns: 100px 2; /* safari and chrome */-moz-columns: 100px 2;"></div>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><strong>Seefeld (4 nights) - Pertisau (3 nights) - Alpbach (4 nights) - Mayrhofen (3 nights)<br /></strong><strong>A superb overview of the Austrian Tyrol,</strong> and an ideal chance for walkers to explore the contrasting hiking terrain in different valleys, from gentle flower filled meadows to beautiful lakeside paths and dramatic Alpine trails with great views. We start with a gentle introduction in the rolling green hills of Seefeld, where you can join an Inghams Wanderwalk, before transferring on to peaceful Pertisau on the scenic western shores of the emerald Lake Achensee, Tyrol’s largest lake. Here you can relax in the lakefront cafés, take a steam train ride, walk some more in the many trails above the village or enjoy a twilight cruise on the lake. On Saturday, transfer to Alpbach village by direct taxi (30 minutes), said to be the most picturesque in the whole of Austria, where you can join free guided walks or simply sit and soak up the views from your hotel. Finish your holiday in lively Mayrhofen (direct taxi transfer 40 minutes) which offers an unrivalled range of activities, excursions and events throughout the summer.</p>
<p>*Hotel Stefanie, Seefeld, Pension Klara, Pertisau, Haus Edelweiss, Alpbach &amp; Strass Garni, Mayrhofen. Other combinations are available.</p>
</div>
</div>
